<TEXT>
here is a glance of the key 
developments in the mass exodus of east germans to west germany 
through hungary 
hungary announces sunday it will allow thousands of vacationing 
east germans to leave for west germany and the exodus through 
austria begins shortly thereafter hungarian border guards at 
hegyeshalom about 120 miles northwest of budapest are instructed 
to let all east germans through with only cursory checks 
east german refugees many crammed in private cars begin 
arriving in passau west germany early monday after an allnight 
drive more than 2000 arrive in west germany by midday the west 
german newspaper die welt reports in its tuesday edition that about 
10000 east germans crossed into the west on monday 
east germanys state news media monday denounces hungarys 
action as illegal and charges that its warsaw pact ally under 
the guise of humanitarism is engaging in organized smuggling of 
humans 
west germanys zdf television network reports east german 
leader erich honecker is in failing health after his gallbladder 
surgery three weeks ago zdf also says critics in the politburo 
reportedly are charging that honecker misjudged the meaning and 
scope of the wave of refugees 
west german chancellor helmut kohl in a speech monday in 
bremen calls on his countrymen to welcome the east german refugees 
and to have faith in the future of a reunified germany 
</TEXT>
