antibiotics and a serum containing hsinghsings antibodies to 
bolster its fragile immune system 
the cub which weighed only 31 ounces at birth was removed from 
its 250pound mother and placed in an oxygenrich incubator there 
it was fed a special formula through a tube into its stomach and 
cuddled by a rubber glove filled with warm water to simulate 
linglings motherly paw 
