president roh taewoo on monday 
proposed new steps toward northsouth korean reunification and said 
he hoped a charter for a korean commonwealth could be signed by 
next august by the longdivided and hostile sides 
i hope that a southnorth summit will take place as quickly as 
possible to successfully launch joint efforts for opening an era 
of fullfledged interkorean cooperation and unification roh said 
in a televised address to the national assembly 
but he added the reality is that it will be impossible to 
achieve unification overnight he urged north korea to abandon 
its policy of unification through communization of the south 
roh said he wants a charter for the commonwealth an interim 
stage for merging the two koreas signed by next august he also 
called for measures to build confidence and control arms in an 
effort to end the arms race between north and south 
there was no immediate response from the communist north and 
