democracy said rohs peace gesture failed to reflect the views of 
all south koreans some of whom demand the removal of us troops 
from the south 
the opposition party called for a detailed and active 
government role in easing military confrontation with north korea 
north korea has demanded the withdrawal of us forces stationed 
in south korea contending american troops are a major obstacle to 
unification talks 
it has called for a confederation under which there would be one 
korea for military and diplomatic matters but each side would 
maintain its own political and social system 
over the past several decades unification talks have been held 
on and off but little progress has been made 
in recent years south korean dissidents have called for stronger 
efforts toward unification they want free travel across the heavily 
guarded border and the immediate withdrawal of the 43000 american 
troops in the south 
a radical student a dissident clergymen and an opposition 
lawmaker are in jail for making unauthorized visits to the north 
rohs new proposal calls for interim governmental bodies equally 
divided between the two koreas changing his earlier position that 
the south should have a larger representation because it has twice 
the population of the north 
the first step in his plan calls for establishing a korean 
national community with the holding of a summit and the signing of 
a national community charter 
the second step would be formation of a korean commonwealth 
made up of a council of presidents a 20member council of 
ministers a 100member council of representatives and a joint 
secretariat 
the secretariat perhaps stationed in a border peace zone 
would help handle routine commonwealth business with liaison 
offices operating in the capitals of the two nations as 
quasidiplomatic missions roh said 
in the final step the commonwealth would draw up a constitution 
and set up elections for a united nation he said 
five years after korea was divided in 1945 the north invaded the 
south starting the 195053 korean war a ceasefire ended the war 
but no peace treaty has been signed 
