president reagan and president bush knew of the exnational security 
advisers activities in the irancontra scandal 
us district judge harold greene directed poindexters attorneys 
to explain to the court by next week how presidential and vice 
presidential documents would corroborate his claims that reagan and 
bush were aware of actions which later led to poindexters 
indictment 
neither a president nor his papers are beyond the reach of the 
law greene said 
the judge ordered independent counsel lawrence walsh to file 
court papers saying what responsibility if any he has to secure 
presidential and vice presidential documents and turn them over to 
poindexter 
under indictment for allegedly covering up oliver norths 
assistance to the nicaraguan contras poindexter says he had no 
motive to conceal norths and his own activities because reagan 
authorized them leading poindexter to believe they were legal 
if these claims of authorization by reagan and knowledge by 
bush are literally correct said greene the documents which 
would support them would be material to the preparation of 
poindexters defense 
poindexter worked directly for the former president met 
with him on an almost daily basis and the alleged violations 
occurred while he was so employed said the judge 
poindexters lawyers have asserted that reagan authorized 
poindexters responses to congressional inquiries about norths 
activities poindexter later was indicted for those responses which 
