that it still looks like well have a parliament that isnt bad as 
a whole 
labor was projected to win 64 seats of the 165 seats its 
socialist ally would add 16 the threeparty nonsocialist alliance 
conservatives christian democrats and center party would get 61 
seats the unpredictable rightwing party of progress would have 
20 with small parties and independents getting a total of four 
seats 
the tendency is clearly toward a nonsocialist majority that 
