that halved inflation in two years to 48 percent and turned a 
balance of payments deficit into a surplus but unemployment nearly 
tripled in the same period to 5 percent and companies went bankrupt 
at the fastest rate since world war ii surveys show oslo to be 
europes most expensive capital 
