always there says professor eric gershwin once allergic 
always allergic 
according to gershwin allergic youngsters are more vulnerable to 
recurrent colds sore throats or ear infections short attention 
spans poor academic performances sleep disturbances poor 
appetite irritability and psychological disturbances 
allergies are certainly a major social psychological and 
financial burden for children and their parents says gershwin 
