and uniroyal inc of middlebury conn merged their tire operations 
on aug 1 1986 
michelin which has us headquarters in greenville sc 
operates eight tire plants in the united states and canada while 
uniroyal goodrich own seven plants in the two countries 
analysts estimated a buyout could cost between 700 million and 
1 billion 
uniroyal goodrich had total sales last year of 22 billion and 
reported profit of 192 million including a onetime gain of 93 
million from the termination of a pension plan during the second 
quarter ended june 30 
the company however lost 7 million during the first quarter of 
this year after incurring additional interest expense from last 
years restructuring which wiped out operating profits the company 
said 
jouppi said it would be logical for michelin to acquire uniroyal 
goodrich because michelin would win the ohio firms market share 
greatly boost its manufacturing capacity and prevent uniroyal 
goodrich from being bought by another competitor 
uniroyal goodrich declined comment on the prospects of 
acquisition by michelin 
