winners were not paid according to the gaming guide issued by 
trump castle hotel amp casino but were instead paid under the actual 
rules of the game 
among the errors was an illustration showing that a gambler who 
puts down money on black is paid off if the ball lands on red and 
that a ball landing on an odd number pays off a bet on an even 
number the philadelphia inquirer said 
the guides were distributed in 1986 1987 and part of 1988 the 
paper said 
regulators knew the guide was inaccurate as early as september 
1986 but fred gushin deputy attorney general for gaming 
enforcement gave trump castle permission to keep distributing the 
booklet until copies ran out the paper said 
no one was cheated here because while the gaming guide 
contained technical errors the game was played according to the 
rules approved by the commission gushin said 
