week by concern that the market was due for at least a pause after 
its sharp rise through the first eight months of the year 
there also has been much talk on wall street that the federal 
reserve will be reluctant to relax its credit policy any further 
over the next several weeks 
fed policymakers are believed to be satisfied that the risk of a 
recession have been averted for now given recent data that showed a 
strongerthanexpected pace of business activity 
nevertheless interest rates declined slightly in the credit 
markets today suggesting that traders believe the economy has room 
to keep on expanding moderately without aggravating inflation or 
