<TEXT>
dominos pizza inc owner tom monaghans 
disclosure that he may sell the company comes at a time when the 
fastfood concerns fastrising star may be dimming an industry 
analyst said monday 
dominos the no 2 pizzamaker in the nation behind pizza hut 
inc is the leader in pizza deliveries 
but analysts say the privately held companys sales growth rate 
has slowed and its profit reportedly declined last year from the 
previous year 
dominos has been on such a fantastic growth rate said gary 
stibel founder of new england consulting a marketing and 
management consulting firm in westport conn 
companies like dominos cannot continue to grow at their 
pace he said 
monaghan who owns 97 percent of the ann arborbased pizza 
delivery company sent a letter last week to about 800 franchise 
owners 16 regional offices and 300 employees at corporate offices 
that he is exploring a sale so he can spend more time doing charity 
work 
but stibel said there may be another reason 
dominos has become principally concerned about the cap on the 
growth of this business he said their share of the total 
universe is beginning to start to flatten out 
dominos spokesman ron hingst said monday he knows of no active 
sale negotiations he hasnt even made a decision to sell it or 
not to sell it he said 
he monaghan has had a number of offers over the years 
hingst said ten to 15 years ago he had an offer from pizza hut 
and turned it down 
although it is second to pizza hut in overall pizza sales 
dominos is the worlds largest in pizza deliveries with 1988 sales 
at 23 billion pizza hut had overall sales of 32 billion in 1988 
but only 20 percent to 30 percent of that was for consumption 
outside its stores 
hingst said dominos sales have set company records every year 
since the early 1980s as the number of its stores grew now 
dominos operates or has franchised 5200 stores worldwide 
the company is privately held and does not publicly report its 
earnings but hingst did not dispute news reports that its profit 
fell to 61 million last year from 77 million the previous year 
dominos dominance of the delivery business is being threatened 
pizza hut with 7000 restaurants began a delivery service out 
of existing sitdown restaurants and other deliveryonly storefronts 
in 1985 
pizza hut spokesman jim schwartz said from corporate headquarters 
in wichita kan that sales from the delivery stores is growing at 
an annual pace of 15 percent to 16 percent 
detroitbased little caesars pizza with about half as many 
stores as dominos is the nations thirdlargest pizza company and 
had sales last year of about 908 million 
dominos has been struggling with some damaging news this year 
its guarantee of 30minute delivery has come under criticism for 
putting delivery time ahead of safe driving dominos conducts 
driver safety classes for its deliverers 
monaghan has come under fire from womens groups critical of his 
outspoken opposition to abortion and the national organization for 
women has organized a national boycott of the chain 
the 52yearold monaghan supports the roman catholic church cs 
mott childrens hospital in ann arbor and the university of michigan 
school of architecture he also founded the dominos foundation 
which has supported healthcare agencies and educational and 
cultural groups 
he also owns the detroit tigers baseball team 
the thought of selling dominos pizza is not a pleasant idea 
monaghan wrote in his letter i must emphasize that it is only a 
possibility at this point 
</TEXT>
