foreign commerce 
after the nearly twohour hearing monday in los angeles federal 
court however rafeedie refused to grant the requested preliminary 
injunction 
the plaintiff has not demonstrated the probability of success 
or that the state act directly regulates foreign commerce 
rafeedie said 
the state statutes involved give insurance departments authority 
to protect insurance policyholders by reviewing insurance industry 
takeovers 
